# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The repo tracks everything needed to REGENERATE EVERY FIGURE from a clone:
#   analysis CSV/JSON summaries, the GNEB MEP bands (final_band.npz + report.json),
#   the 3Q/ZZ reference spin states, and all scripts.
# Bulk solver by-products are excluded -- they are regenerable with
# run_campaign.py / gneb_barrier_width_sweep.py (both resumable):
#   MD trajectories (*.h5, ~70 GB), per-run configs, per-run relaxed states,
#   disorder realizations, and per-image GNEB intermediates.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Large binary time series
*.h5
*.hdf5

# Bulk per-run solver by-products
**/runs/
**/quenches/
**/configs/
**/initial_states/
**/disorder_files/
**/seeds/
**/relax/

# Per-image GNEB intermediates (the converged band is kept as final_band.npz)
**/img_*.txt
**/*_H.txt
**/band_e.csv
**/band_manifest.txt
**/*_in.txt
**/defect.txt
*.param
**/positions.txt
**/initial_spins.txt

# Python / editor / OS
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
.DS_Store
*.swp

# LaTeX build artifacts (keep .tex, .bib, .pdf, .png)
*.aux
*.bbl
*.blg
*.fdb_latexmk
*.fls
*.log
*.out
*.synctex.gz
*.toc

# Symlinks into the ClassicalSpin_Cpp solver checkout
/build
/util
